title: 820-00923 20v 0.78A No USB activity CPU code 1V
message:
Clean board, had 2 caps on PP5V_S4 getting hot but not full short, after removing them and installing new U7560 I got 20V on charger but CPU core voltage does NOT go from 1V to 0.6 Tried good known bios with Medusa 3 also but same thing.

pp3v3_g3h 3.4v
ppbus_g3h 13.07v
pp5v5_s5 5.12v
pp3v3_s5 3.35v
pm_slp_s4_l 3.3v
smc_reset_l 3.4
all_sys_pwrgd 3.2v
pp5v_s0_fan_conn 5.1v
pp5v_s0_vcore1 5.1v
pp5v_s0_vcore2 5.1v
pm_slp_s5_l 3.3v
rtc_reset_l 3.1v
pch_srtcrst_l 3.1
pch_intruder 2.8v
PLT_RST_L 3.3V

CPU is the only thing that gets hot now.

title: 820-00923 20v 0.78A No USB activity CPU code 1V
message:
Probably CPU internal problem.
You can try to heat with quality flux, in case of accumulated crap underneath.

Did you test the board alone on the desk?

title: 820-00923 20v 0.78A No USB activity CPU code 1V
message:
Tried the flux trick, same problem.

Yes, all my test and measurements are done with the board alone unless I need to test something else additionally.

Thanks!

title: 820-00923 20v 0.78A No USB activity CPU code 1V
message: If you can't find any damaged component in the CPU area, then CPU should be bad...
